{"key":"processedPost-13263655","value":{"id":13263655,"first":13263499,"last":13263967,"when":1285774247,"utime":"09/29/10 06:30 PM","content":"Sometimes turning them over will cause a small air pocket to form at the bottom(now top) of the jar allowing the rest to finish colonizing.&nbsp; However, it disturbs the verm filter when you do this, so leave them upside down until finished.&nbsp; If you flip them back and forth, you allow contaminants to work their way down the filter and into the rice flour, ruining the cake.<br />It's best to use 1/2 pint wide mouth jars so you don't ever have this problem.<br />RR","title":"Re: BRF cakes upside down?"}}